data: {"type":"response.output_text.done","content_index":0,"item_id":"msg_0f43cf97373323340069cc4916a820819682b986d58e1ba5f4","logprobs":[],"output_index":1,"sequence_number":79,"text":"Here are the very latest updates on London Underground (Tube) services and related transport disruptions as of today, Tuesday 31 March 2026:\n\n---\n\n##  Live Status Overview\n\n- Most Underground lines are operating normally, with a **good service** across the network.([tubenotifications.co.uk](https://tubenotifications.co.uk/line-status))\n- **Central line** is experiencing **minor delays** due to an earlier faulty train at Bond Street.([tubenotifications.co.uk](https://tubenotifications.co.uk/line-status))\n- The **Docklands Light Railway (DLR)** also has **minor delays**, caused by an earlier faulty train near Westferry.([tubenotifications.co.uk](https://tubenotifications.co.uk/line-status))\n\n---\n\n##  Specific Line Notices & Planned Disruptions\n\n- **Barons Court Station**:\n  - Eastbound services are suspended until **Sunday 7 June**. Passengers heading east from Barons Court should use westbound District or Piccadilly line trains and change at Hammersmith. Those heading *to* eastbound Barons Court should alight at West Kensington (District) or Earl’s Court (Piccadilly) and change for westbound services.([standard.co.uk](https://www.standard.co.uk/news/london/victoria-station-delays-tfl-tube-b1276940.html))\n\n- **Victoria Station**:\n  - Reduced escalator service to the Victoria line is in effect until **late May 2026** due to ongoing replacement works.([tfl.gov.uk](https://tfl.gov.uk/tube-dlr-overground/status/))\n\n---\n\n##  Weekend & Upcoming Easter Disruptions (Early April)\n\nTransport planning for the **Easter weekend** (3–6 April) indicates several lines will either be closed or partially suspended:\n\n- **Bakerloo Line**: No service between **Stonebridge Park** and **Harrow & Wealdstone** on **Saturday 4 April** and **Easter Sunday 5 April**. Replacement bus service (718) will be in operation.([trafficdelays.co.uk](https://www.trafficdelays.co.uk/london-trains/))\n\n- **Lioness Line**: Also suspended between **Euston** and **Watford Junction** on the same dates, with supplementary bus services (720) provided.([trafficdelays.co.uk](https://www.trafficdelays.co.uk/london-trains/))\n\n- **District Line**: Closed between **Earls Court** and **Kensington (Olympia)**, and between **Whitechapel** and **Upminster** over **Good Friday (3 April)**, **Saturday (4 April)**, **Easter Sunday (5 April)**, and **Easter Monday (6 April)**. Alternative routes and buses will be available.([trafficdelays.co.uk](https://www.trafficdelays.co.uk/london-trains/))\n\n- **Hammersmith & City Line**: Fully closed over the same Easter period (3–6 April).([trafficdelays.co.uk](https://www.trafficdelays.co.uk/london-trains/))\n\n- **Waterloo & City Line**: Operates only Monday to Friday (early morning to post-midnight). No service on weekends or bank/public holidays, including the upcoming Easter weekend.([trafficdelays.co.uk](https://www.trafficdelays.co.uk/london-trains/))\n\n---\n\n##  Other Disruptions & Accessibility Issues\n\n- **Station accessibility and stepped-free access** issues:\n  - **Barking**, **Caledonian Road & Barnsbury**, **Gospel Oak**, **Hounslow West**, **Hendon Central**, **Langdon Park**, **West Silvertown**, and **Woolwich Arsenal** are all currently affected by lift faults or maintenance, limiting step-free access.([tfl.gov.uk](https://tfl.gov.uk/tube-dlr-overground/status/))\n\n- **Wembley Area**:\n  - Ongoing modernization of the footbridge at **Clapham Junction** (March 2026–Nov 2027). Users should allow extra time for their journeys.([tfl.gov.uk](https://tfl.gov.uk/tube-dlr-overground/status/))\n  - **Wembley Central**: Today (Tuesday 31 March), heavy congestion is expected due to the **England vs Japan** match. The main entrance will be exit-only temporarily, with step-free access via an alternative entrance.([tfl.gov.uk](https://tfl.gov.uk/tube-dlr-overground/status/))\n  - **Wembley Park Station**: Lift access from street to ticket hall is unavailable until **Autumn 2026**, though alternate level routes remain. Entry restrictions apply today due to the event; use Olympic Way for entry.([tfl.gov.uk](https://tfl.gov.uk/tube-dlr-overground/status/))\n\n---\n\n##  Summary Table\n\n| Line / Station          | Current Status / Notice                                                                 |\n|-------------------------|------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|\n| Central Line            | Minor delays (Bond Street faulty train)                                                 |\n| DLR                     | Minor delays (fault near Westferry)                                                     |\n| Other Tube Lines        | Good service generally across the network                                               |\n| Barons Court Station    | Eastbound services suspended until 7 June                                               |\n| Victoria Station        | Reduced escalator access to Victoria line until late May                                |\n| Easter weekend closures | Bakerloo, District, Lioness, Hammersmith & City, and Waterloo & City lines affected     |\n| Accessibility issues    | Multiple stations with lift faults (see above)                                          |\n| Clapham Junction        | Footbridge works until Nov 2027 — allow extra time                                      |\n| Wembley Central/Park    | Event-related congestion, altered access, ongoing lift works                            |\n\n---\n\nLet me know if you'd like planned updates for specific dates or tailored assistance for your journey."}

